summary: This is a domestic witness travel request form from an AUSA to the SDNY Victim/Witness Unit, dated November 14, 2021, for a fact witness to appear in the United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell case for trial preparation. The witness is scheduled to be in New York from December 5 to December 8, 2021.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: The defendant in the criminal case referenced in the travel request form (United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell).

events.title: Witness Travel for Trial Preparation
events.description: A fact witness is scheduled to arrive in SDNY for trial preparation in the Ghislaine Maxwell case.

keyFacts: The document is a travel request form for a fact witness in the United States v. Ghislaine Maxwell case (Docket No. 20 Cr. 330).
The witness is scheduled to be in New York from December 5 to December 8, 2021, for trial preparation.
The witness is identified as a fact witness, not an expert witness, and is not a victim-witness, federal employee, or facing criminal charges.
The form indicates the witness requires hotel accommodations but no unusual travel expenses.
The document references DOJ Instruction 1300.01.01 for witness travel procedures.
